DENGUE/DHF COLOMBIA (CALI) (02)
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Dengue/DHF - Colombia (Cali) 980125224011
Date: Mon, 26 Jan 1998 07:13:10 +0000
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background information on dengue in Colombia were extracted
from the GIDEON software program:
Potential for transmission exists along the Atlantic coast, Magdalena River
Valley, Cauca River Valley, Putumayo Intendancy and Cordillera Oriental
slopes. 83% of elementary school children in Cali were seropositive in 1997.
Dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) was first reported in 1985. 3,929 cases of
DHF (32 fatal) were reported during 1981 to 1996.
Year Dengue DHF Fatalities
